post_text: Reminder Parents and Students, apply for your Chromebook and/or Hotspot today!
shared_text:
Mercedes Schools
August 4 at 8:29 AM ·

Mercedes ISD is committed to ensuring that students have home access to online instructional materials during the upcoming period of remote instruction and throughout the 2020-2021 school year.

About Home CONNECT
To ensure highly-effective in-school and remote instruction, Mercedes ISD is implementing initiatives designed to promote successful communication and collaboration between students and teachers for all households under the Home CONNECT program. Some of these initiative include:

-Hotspot and Chromebook device loans for households
-Effective online instruction via Google Classroom platform
-Google Classroom training resources parents and guardians
-Mobile Internet access via school and neighborhood bus-powered wifi
-Call-based technical support for households (regular and extended hours)

To begin the hotspot and/or Chromebook request process, please visit the MISD website at www.misdtx.net and click on the Home CONNECT link.

post_text:
Mercedes ISD se compromete a garantizar que los estudiantes tengan acceso en el hogar a los materiales de instrucción en línea durante el próximo período de instrucción remota y durante todo el año escolar 2020-2021.

Para garantizar una instrucción remota y altamente efectiva en la escuela, Mercedes ISD está implementando iniciativas diseñadas para promover la comunicación y colaboración exitosa entre estudiantes y maestros para todos los hogares bajo el programa Home CONNECT. Algunas de estas iniciativas incluyen:

-Préstamos de puntos de acceso y computadoras Chromebook para hogares
-Instrucción en línea efectiva a través de la plataforma Google Classroom
-Entrenamiento para padres y guardianes de Google classroom.
-Acceso a Internet móvil a través de puntos de acceso por autobuses escolares
-Soporte técnico por teléfono para hogares (horario regular y extendido)

Para comenzar el proceso de solicitud de punto de acceso y / o Chromebook, visite el sitio web de MISD en www.misdtx.net y haga clic en el enlace Home CONNECT.

Dear MISD Parents, to help us prepare for the 2020-2021 school year, we are gathering information regarding internet access and transportation. Your assistance is needed to ensure we get the most accurate data regarding our student needs.

The information is essential for planning for our 2020-2021 school year. We appreciate your time and effort.

To begin the 2-minute survey, please visit us at www.misdtx.net

La información es esencial para planificar nuestro año escolar 2020-2021. Agradecemos su tiempo y esfuerzo.

Para comenzar la encuesta de 2 minutos, visítenos en www.misdtx.net

Family and Community Engagement Mercedes-ACE is at Mercedes High School.
May 11 at 1:34 PM · Mercedes, TX ·

Since Adopt a Valley Graduate isn’t excepting any more post I thought I just put it on my page.
Hello Everyone, this is my son John Michael Ortega. He is a 2020 Senior at Mercedes High School. John is a 2 time Regional Qualifier and a 2 time State Qualifier. He placed 1st in all six powerlifting meets he competed in this 2020 season. John is ranked #1 in State in his weight class. Johns goal was to bring a boys State title to MHS. Unfortunately this pandemic took that opportunity away from him. Nevertheless John will be attending Texas A&M University Kingsville this fall where he will pursue his career in Criminal Justice.🏋🏽👨🏽‍🎓

#COVID19 lives on droplets in the lungs of people with the virus, even if they don’t have symptoms. When infected people breathe, the virus enters the air. If you can’t #StayHome, wear a mask/scarf/bandana, stay 6 feet apart, and wash your hands. #DontGoViral

#COVID19 vive de gotas en los pulmones de las personas con el virus incluso si no tienen síntomas.Cuando las personas contagiadas respiran, el virus entra al aire.Si no puedes quedarte en casa #StayHome, use una bufanda/pañuelo, manténgase a 6 pies de distancia y lávese las manos
text:
#COVID19 lives on droplets in the lungs of people with the virus, even if they don’t have symptoms. When infected people breathe, the virus enters the air. If you can’t #StayHome, wear a mask/scarf/bandana, stay 6 feet apart, and wash your hands. #DontGoViral

#COVID19 vive de gotas en los pulmones de las personas con el virus incluso si no tienen síntomas.Cuando las personas contagiadas respiran, el virus entra al aire.Si no puedes quedarte en casa #StayHome, use una bufanda/pañuelo, manténgase a 6 pies de distancia y lávese las manos

Announcement:
Mercedes ISD has a new HELPLINE to report any potential or real threats or wrongdoings against any Mercedes school. Reporting can be done anonymously by telephone, smartphone, or computer by calling the helpline, using the app or visiting the website.

Remember, If you see something, say something! The Safe School Helpline is a convenient, confidential way for anyone to report information about situations that might affect safety at our schools. You can call/text/submit online any time of the day or night to report concerns about unsafe or potentially disruptive activities or situations including drug or alcohol abuse, weapons, harassment, bullying or threats. All calls/texts/submissions are confidential.

Visit https://www.misdtx.net/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1625242&type=d&pREC_ID=1810318 for more information.

Call:800-418-6423 (800-4-1-VOICE ext. 359)
TEXT: 66746, TIPS
Online: www.safeschoolhelpline.com

#SafeSchoolHelpline

post_text:
Mercedes ISD Band Members competed in UIL Solo and Ensemble Season with 12 First Division medals earned and all advancing to the state level in June.

Jose Vasquez (12) Trombone Soloist *Advancing to state

Ricardo Balvanera (10) Trombone Soloist * advancing to state

Trombone Trio: Mario Bustamante (10), Tyler Galvan (12), and Jose Vasquez (12)

Tuba/Euphonium Ensemble: Frank Alvarado (9), Juan Martel (12), Stephanie Moreno (11), Aiden Ybarra (11)

Saxophone Trio: Matthew Ayala (10), Eulalia Medrano (10), Liberty Ybarra (12)

This brings the final count of first division medals to a perfect 100 members of the band, orchestra, and mariachi earning medals. There will also be 15 soloists advancing to the state level; and 9 small ensembles. This will be held at UT Austin on June 1, 2020.

post_text:
On February 6, 2020, Jayden Cruz, 5th-grade student at Taylor Elementary, was among 50 other contestants who participated in the MISD Spelling Bee, and was crowned the 2020 MISD Spelling Bee Champion by correctly spelling the word “v-i-c-i-n-i-t-y” in a lone round!! Jayden will now compete at the Regional Spelling Contest on Saturday, March 7th at Texas State Technical College for the chance to advance to the Scripps National Spelling Bee near Washington, DC.
Spelling Bee Coordinator, Mrs. Lisa Sanchez, would like to congratulate Jayden, his parents Ernesto and Tammy Jo Cruz, Principal David Aguirre, and his Spelling Coach, Mrs. Yvonne Smith.

Way to go, Jayden, and GOOD LUCK AT REGIONALS!!

post_text: On February 8, 2020, the Mercedes Winter Guard competed at the Texas Educational Colorguard Association Competition in Hidalgo, Texas. Their show entitled “A Wicked Night” tells the story of individuals awakening at night and encountering a dark presence that makes them become wicked. They performed very well at the contest that they earned 3rd place out of 9 teams in the Regional AA Classification. Their next contest will take place at Mission HS on February 29, 2020!

post_text: Thank you to our MISD Safe Schools Department, Mercedes EMT, our Lead Nurse and all our campuses nurses. Student safety is our number one priority.
shared_text:
Family and Community Engagement Mercedes-ACE is at Sgt. William G. Harrell Middle School.
January 16 at 8:39 AM · Mercedes, TX ·

Valley schools implementing “Stop The Bleed” training
The Stop The Bleed kit includes a tourniquet, gauze, gloves, scissors and instructions on how to use the equipment. The Mercedes ISD is making it their mission to get everyone prepared. Employees are trained to use the kits, but the superintendent says students also need to know how to respond.
https://www.kveo.com/news/local-news/valley-schools-implementing-stop-the-bleed-training/amp/?__twitter_impression=true

post_text: Honored to have Judge Keno Vasquez at Mercedes High School. Great experience for our students and staff.
shared_text:
Hidalgo County Sheriff's Office
December 6, 2019 at 10:51 AM ·

Court is in session!!!

Hidalgo County Sheriff Deputies and Detention Officers are assisting Judge Keno Vasquez of the 398th District Court with Courts in Schools at the Mercedes High School.

Continuing to educate our youth on the dangers and consequences of bad choices is a top priority of Judge Vasquez and Sheriff J.E. “Eddie” Guerra!

Special thanks to Nueces County Sheriff J.C. Hooper, Nueces County 319th District Court Judge David Stith, and 347th District Court
Judge Missy Medary for attending and learning about the courts in schools program.

#myHCSO #CourtInSchools
